dialog.text: Oda sensei! In [[Wano Country|Wano Kuni]], [[Basil Hawkins|Hawkins]] is riding on a really cool animal. What the name of that animal? Is it only available in Wano? - P. N. Shian

Yeah, [[Animal Species/Wano Country Saga#Komashika|Komashika]], [[Komachiyo]] the [[Animal Species/Wano Country Saga#Komainu|Komainu]], [[Animal Species/Wano Country Saga#Komadane|Komadane]], [[Animal Species/Wano Country Saga#Komatori|Komatori]] are unique to Wano. The thing they have in common is the flame-like fur. There are a lot more different types of these animals, but I'm not sure if they will get a chance to appear in the story.

qa.summary: Hawkins is riding a Komashika, unique to Wano, known for flame-like fur; other Wano animals like Komachiyo, Komainu, Komadane, Komatori might also appear.

dialog.text: "Simsim" actually means "sesame" (in arabic). Long ago, in certain places, people believed sesame contained magic and it was mysterious. In "[[Wikipedia:Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves|Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves]]" there is the phrase "[[Wikipedia:Open Sesame (phrase)|Open Sesame]]". Did you hear it before? It's pronounced افتح يا سمسم in arabic. Sanji put their "taste" and "power" into the cream. Although Sanji was unaware that cream was part of [[Charlotte Linlin|Big Mom]]'s favorite food "[[Foods#Semla|Semla]]" too. I'm sure the power of simsim Cream awakened Big Mom's old memories and had a big impact on the battle.
matches: Wikipedia:Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves|Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves

character_names.text: Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves

qa.summary: Simsim in Arabic means "sesame" and Sanji's cream in that chapter contained the 'taste' and 'power' of simsim, affecting Big Mom in a significant way.

dialog.text: I asked the staff. Among the identities that can be confirmed are "{{Ruby|踊雀伍関|おどりジャンゴぜき}}" (Odori [[Jango]]-zeki), "{{Ruby|雹三海関|ヒョウゾウうみぜき}}" ([[Hyouzou|Hyōzō]] Umi-zeki), "{{Ruby|猛岩斧関|モーガンおのぜき}}" ([[Morgan|Mōgan]] Ono-zeki), "{{Ruby|海四怒関|マリンフォードぜき}}" ([[Marineford|Marinfōdo]]-zeki), "{{Ruby|下打津関|ゲダツぜき}}" ([[Gedatsu]]-zeki), "{{Ruby|氷馬喰関|アイスバーグぜき}}" ([[Iceburg|Aisubāgu]]-zeki), "{{Ruby|輪八関|ワイパーぜき}}" ([[Wyper|Waipā]]-zeki). The staff also told me that there was a "{{Ruby|判馬具関|ハンバーグぜき}}" ([[Hamburg|Hanbāgu]]-zeki) in [[Chapter 917]], "めし{{Ruby|処|どころ}}{{Ruby|羽が屋|パガヤ}}" (Meshidokoro [[Pagaya]])" in [[Chapter 931]], and graves for "{{Ruby|苦炉尾火|クロオビ}}" ([[Kuroobi]]) and "{{Ruby|画井門|ガイモン}}" ([[Gaimon]]) in [[Chapter 934]]. Well done to both pirates!! Hahaha.{{-}}

qa.summary: Oda confirms the hidden words as 'Jango', 'Hyouzou', 'Kaidou', 'Gedatsu', 'Pagaya', 'Kuroobi' and 'Gaimon' in specific chapters, while adding a joke at the end.

dialog.text: Mixed baths... Geat Oda-sensei, mixed baths... The [[Flower Capital]]'s mixed baths public baths have mixed bathing... I'm curious as to how mixed bathing works... can I go there? - P. N. Hayato Nokou

You're are being driven by your desires, aren't you!! You pig!! This is culture! Japan still has hot spring baths. Back during the Edo period, mixed baths were very common everywhere in Japan. Wano is inspired by Japan, so I absolutely had to include them... I really couldn't not include them, I swear. My heart was unwilling, but I had to paint it. Whoops, sorry, my nose is bleeding. You got some toilet paper for me?

qa.summary: Oda explains that mixed bathing was common in Edo period Japan and is included in Wano as a cultural reference, while jokingly admitting to being unwilling but had to include it.

dialog.text: Hello. In [[Chapter 905]] of [[Volume 90]], when [[Belo Betty|Betty]] and [[Koala]] were talking, Koala had a girl with black hair on the left side. The girl also had a mechanical arm. What is her name? Please tell me! - P. N. Emerald Rabbit

Aaaah... There are 5 Commanders in the [[Revolutionary Army]], of the [[East Blue|East]], [[West Blue|West]], [[North Blue|North]], [[South Blue|South]] and [[Grand Line|G (Grand Line)]] armies. [[Emporio Ivankov|Ivankov]] is the Commander of G army, and [[Inazuma]] is his assistant, the deputy commander. This girl is [[Ahiru]], the deputy commander of the East army and the assistant of Belo Betty.

[[File:SBS 93 Clouds.png|thumb|200px]]

qa.summary: The girl with black hair and a mechanical arm in Chapter 905 is Ahiru, the deputy commander of the East army and assistant of Belo Betty.

dialog.text: Hey, about the clouds in Wano Country... ah! Isn't the shape of those farts different from the way Oda usually draws farts - P. N. King that really loves Cora-san

You again? Why do you keep thinking that what's drawn in the sky is my farts? IT'S CLOUDS!! THEY'RE CLOUDS FLOATING IN THE SKY!! As you can imagine Wano Country has a different atmosphere! Because it is Wano Country, I felt it'd be appropriate to make it look like old that Ukiyo-e screens, in other words I'm just doing different farts from usual. Prrrrtt~!

qa.summary: Oda clarifies that the shapes in the sky are clouds, not farts, and explains that they are drawn differently to match Wano's atmosphere.

dialog.text: When [[Kaidou]] turned into a dragon, did he like float in the air? - P. N. I am came the crane from that time
I've heard dragons fly by grabbing onto clouds and carrying themselves through the air. So because of that, Kaidou generates clouds and flies across skies with them.

qa.summary: Kaidou generates clouds and flies using them, inspired by the idea of dragons grabbing onto clouds to soar through the sky.

dialog.text: Thinking back about O-[[Tama]]'s house, there's this tanuki that looks like a bunbuku kettle, but I like to think he wasn't domesticated with her power. I don't think it's tamed with O-Tama's ability. If you're ever in need about wild ideas for your beautiful chapters, how about I help you out? - P. N. Ehara Ryouta

So you've noticed? The fellow existence I mean. In reality, it kettle that ate the [[Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Tanuki]]. Since it was a kettle precious to [[Kozuki Sukiyaki|Hitetsu]], even now that it gotten these powers, both Hitetsu and Tama are still emotionally attached. Also it will feel hot if you put it on fire, so it is a pet that can’t be used to boil water anymore. But, one more thing, I was hoping someone would notice it, but no one mentioned it. So I will announce it right here!! If you look carefully, Mr. [[Bunbuku]] is actually... SITTING ON ITS OWN BALLS!! LMAO I can't believe no one ever noticed it!! I laugh as I drew it alone!! [[File:SBS 93 Newgate.png|thumb|200px]]
matches: Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Tanuki

normal_links.text: Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Tanuki

qa.summary: Oda reveals that the tanuki is actually a kettle that ate the Inu Inu no Mi, Model: Tanuki, and is emotionally attached to Hitetsu and Tama, while also adding a humorous detail about its design.

dialog.text: I watched [[One Piece Film: Gold|film Gold]] that I've recorded, and I saw that [[Sakazuki]] tell [[Rob Lucci|Lucci]] "You've become more erotic". What does he mean by "erotic"? - P. N. Min Domu

Day after day, people will become more erotic and our dear Rob Lucci-san is no different. In that scene, it seems Sakazuki had been Rob Lucci appearing rather erotically on a magazine, so he asked him "can you lend me an issue?". I always thought that was a powerful scene... HE SAID "HEROIC"!!! "YOU'VE BECOME MUCH MORE HEROIC" IS WHAT HE MEANT!!! [[File:SBS 93 Scabbards.png|thumb|300px|''"The question is, how will we remain in contact? I have heard that in foreign lands, they use a kind of 'snail'..."'']]
matches: File:SBS 93 Scabbards.png|thumb|300px|''"The question is, how will we remain in contact? I have heard that in foreign lands, they use a kind of 'snail'..."''

qa.summary: Sakazuki meant to say 'heroic', not 'erotic', as he saw Lucci on a magazine and asked for a copy.

dialog.text:
I want to ask something Oda-san. When we were in [[Zou]], [[Kin'emon]] didn't seem to know about the [[Den Den Mushi|Den Den Mushi or snail transponders]]. But when we came to Wano Kuni we saw similar type of snails only smaller in size. Did new communication methods got discovered in Wano kuni in those the 20 years? - P. N. Top Ship Captain Ota-kun

[[File:SBS 93 Usopp and Tanishi.png|thumb|left|200px]]
matches: Den Den Mushi|Den Den Mushi or snail transponders

dialog.text:
That's right. As [[Usopp]] explain in [[Chapter 934]], this is a telepathic-wave-sending "[[Animal Species/Wano Country Saga#Tanishi|Tanishi]]" which is used to communicate in Wano. It became popular during the 20 years when Kin'emon and the others were absent. Now it has become a common communication method in the Wano Country. There is also a "Light Scroll Tanishi" similar to "Video Den Den Mushi". But there seems to be a downside, that is, the wavelengths is slightly weaker than the normal snail transponders...

All right! Time up!! SBS next volume!! There is a notice of the movie STAMPEDE behind!!{{-}}

character_names.text: Den Den Mushi or snail transponders

qa.summary: In Wano Kuni, a telepathic-wave-sending Tanishi is used for communication, becoming popular during the 20 years when Kin'emon and others were absent, with a downside of weaker wavelengths.
